        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ḱīnyg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ḱīnyg</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kinugæ</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>kiwnugæ</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>книга</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>book</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>письмо</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>letter</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ḱīnyg zonyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>уметь читать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>to know how to read</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>(Wærxæg) sæ astæw badtæj ma ḱiwnuguti kastæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(Уархаг) сидел посреди них и читал книги</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(Uarhag) sat in the middle of them and read books</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            76</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æ ew onæbæl kiwnugfinst, e ’nnæbæl ʒiwaræ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на одной его лопатке написанная книга (?), на другой — крест</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a book (?) is a written on one of his shoulder blades, a cross is
                                drawn on the other one</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">из дигорского фольклора</biblScope><biblScope
                                xml:lang="en">from Digor folklore</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Piran st’oly farsmæ badtī æmæ cydær q˳yna ḱīng˳ytæ rafældax-bafældax
                            kodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Пиран сидел за столом и перебирал какие-то заплесневелые книги</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Piran was sitting at the table and sorting through some moldy
                                books</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mæ fyrtæj ḱīnyg rajston</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>получил письмо от сына</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(I) received a letter from my son</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>somīxagæn ḱīnyg nyffystoj dæs æmæ ssæʒ tūmanyl</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>написали армянину расписку на тридцать туманов</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(I) gave the Armenian a receipt for thirty tomans</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>62</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Неотделимо от <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>книга</w></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">кънига</w></mentioned>). Последнее, всего вернее,— из <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼnik</w>
                        <gloss><q>печать</q></gloss></mentioned> (см. <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>664</biblScope></bibl>). Осетинское
                    слово следует рассматривать как старое заимствование из русского %iкънига%i, к
                    которому оно ближе по форме и значению, чем к арм. %ik’nik%i. Для объяснения
                    звуковой формы осетинского слова следует допустить метатезу гласных %i*kuniga%i
                    → %i*kinugæ%i, ср. колебание <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mystūlæg"/> и <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_mustælæg"/> ‘ласка (животное)’.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>11,
                        41</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>69, 521, 527</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_LUÅ"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XIX 7 19
                            сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XIX 7 19
                    ff.</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is inseparable from <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>книга</w>
                        <gloss><q>book</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/>
                        <w>kъniga</w>
                        <gloss><q>book</q></gloss></mentioned>). The latter is most likely from
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼnik</w>
                        <gloss><q>stamp</q></gloss></mentioned> (see <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Berneker"/><biblScope>664</biblScope></bibl>). The Ossetic
                    word should be viewed as an old borrowing from Russian %iкънига%i, to which it
                    is closer in form and meaning than to Armenian %ik’nik%i. In order to explain
                    the Ossetic sound form, one should assume the metathesis of vowels %i*kuniga%i →
                    %i*kinugæ%i, cf. the variation <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mystūlæg"/> and
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_mustælæg"/> ‘weasel’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>11, 41</biblScope></bibl>.—
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>69, 521,
                            527</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_LUÅ"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XIX 7 19 сл.</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">XIX 7 19 ff.</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
